Definition: a standard for judging when freedom of speech can be abridged
Example: no one has a right to shout `fire' in a crowded theater when there is no fire because such an action would pose a clear and present danger to public safety
Synonyms: danger, a, standard, for, judging, when, freedom, of, speech, can, be, abridged, no, one, has, right, to, shout, fire, in, crowded, theater, there, is, because, such, an, action, would, pose, clear, and, present, public, safety
Category: noun.state
